[1] France, SBV confirmed
Date: Fri, 27 Jan 2012
Source: French Ministry of Agriculture - News [Transl, summarised, edited]
http://agriculture.gouv.fr/maladies-animales,11003


Schmallenberg virus identified in sheep in the northeast of France

-----------------------------------------------------
The presence of SBV has been confirmed in lambs on 13 farms in 6 departments of the North of France (departments No 52 [Haute Marne], 54 [Meurthe et Moselle], 57 [Moselle], 62 [Pas de Calais], 76 [Seine Maritime], 80 [Somme]). [For an interactive map of France showing all departments, see
http://www.cartesfrance.fr/carte-france-departement/carte-france-departements.html].

At the onset of SBV in Europe, DGAL (France's Animal Health and Welfare Protection) set in motion a surveillance, through the national platform for animal health epidemiological surveillance, to detect the earliest possible arrival of the disease in France. Sick animals on affected farms were reported by the practitioners to the departmental services. The Animal Health Laboratory at Maisons-Alfort acquired the ability to carry out SBV diagnosis.

--
