[2] Germany, update
Date: Fri, 27 Jan 2012
Source: FLI web-site [German, transl, summarised, edited]
http://www.fli.bund.de/no_cache/de/startseite/aktuelles/tierseuchengeschehen/schmallenberg-virus.html

Current information on the "Schmallenberg virus" [SBV] in Germany
-----------------------------------------------------------------
SBV in animals has already been identified on 106 German farms. this includes 8 cattle, 92 sheep and 6 goat farms. The cases occurred in the states of North Rhine-Westphalia (6 cattle, 57 sheep, 2 goat holdings), Lower Saxony (1 cattle, 23 sheep, 2 goat holdings), Hesse (5 sheep, 1 goat), Schleswig-Holstein (5 sheep holdings), Rhineland-Palatinate (1 bison, 2 sheep holdings) and Baden-Wuerttemberg (one goat holding).

A map of SBV in Germany, updated 27 Jan 2012, is available at <ttp://www.fli.bund.de/fileadmin/dam_uploads/tierseuchen/Schmallenberg_Virus/Karten/Map_Schmallenberg_20120127.jpg>.

